						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged at the end. It records a gift of 15 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Gōkarṇattu-Mahādēva at Tiruvēḷpūr in Kavira-nāḍu (?) a subdivision of Valla-nāḍu (No. 41, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ins.</hi>, Texts). This donor (name not clear) seems to have been a resident of Śiṟukuḷattūr.</p>						

						</summary>
